      <description>As a ranger half elf of tunare that already got the short deal -- compared to woodelf / karana -- on tradeskill on creation by my own ignorance (can't fault the devs for me not knowing that another race and deity was preferential for a wellrounded toon), I would very much like to see this issue getting some proper balance between races and smithing/tailoring. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Meaning that cross races:&lt;br&gt;1. number of drops needed for the same slot has to be the same for both tailoring and smithing&lt;br&gt;2. drop rate for the items has to be the same&lt;br&gt;3. number of mobs that they drop from has to be the same&lt;br&gt;4. spawnrate of the mobs has to be the same&lt;br&gt;5. accessability to the mobs has to be the same (keys, travel, clearing, SI, etc.)&lt;br&gt;6. level requirement for the hunting grounds has to be the same&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Until the condition for farming the drops is tweaked to be generally the same, tradeskilling for tailoring and smithing is greatly unbalanced.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The solution would be to just use the same drop for all the races and instead add it as a random drop from any mob in all the older zones for the player level that the armor drop is for -- zonewide randoms with a uncommon but not rare drop rate. Keep the GM drops to the instances, but even out the recipies to need the same number of drops for tailoring and smithing.</description>
