    <item>
      <title>Re: No ETA on Don Cultural Drop Rate fixes.</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=16412#M16412</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I still am of the opinion a conversion NPC would be a better answer than trying to tweak the drop rates all over the place.&amp;nbsp; Programming such an NPC would take very little time at all.&amp;nbsp; 4 of item x (at level y) could be turned into 1 of item z (at level y).&amp;nbsp; Or require an additional item to do the conversion or create a new TS recipe to do the conversion. For example,&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;2 Metallic Drake Scales + 1 silk swatch + 1 vial of purified mana-&amp;gt; 1 coarse silk swatch&lt;BR&gt;2 Glossy Drake Hides + 1 silk swatch + 1 vial of purified mana -&amp;gt; 1 coarse silk swatch&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;1 Metallic Drake Scale + 1 supple corrupted drake hide + acid wash -&amp;gt; 1 Glossy Drake Hide&lt;BR&gt;1 Coarse silk swatches + 1 supple corrupted drake hide + acid wash -&amp;gt; 1 Glossy Drake Hide&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;1 Glossy Drake Hides + 1 blackened drake scale + 1 celestial temper -&amp;gt; 1 Metallic Drake Scale&lt;BR&gt;1 Coarse silk swatches + 1 blackened drake scale + 1 celestial temper -&amp;gt; 1 Metallic Drake Scale&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Put the NPC in lavastorm in the Wayfarer's camp... or allow players to do this with trivial of 200? 250? 300? (No hard success cap though ... that's saved for making the actual GM armor.)&amp;nbsp; I kept the ingrediant list to 4 (or less) in order to make the hand-in NPC concept easier to implement.&amp;nbsp; Of course, variations on this theme are possible ... and a fair number of my choices are somewhat arbitrary (though not completely without logic).&lt;BR&gt;Required conversions: 6.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;_____________&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;So, how does this work for lower level cultural?&amp;nbsp; I'll use an Iksar example as it is what I know best ... ;-7&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;For each and every race, there is an essence which is used to create their cultural needle.&amp;nbsp; So, let's use that fact in designing the conversion:&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;3 Master level smithing components + 1 cabilis essence -&amp;gt; 1 great reptile tooth&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Master level smithing components: Pile of Gravel, Midnight Stone, Small Brick of Yttrium Ore, Great Reptile tooth&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Given there are approximately 4 base components at each level (3 possible conversion), 3 levels, 3 types of base drops (silk, leather, metal) and 11 races, the NPC would have to take approximately 297 combinations and return the correct item for a given race.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;If you have a philosophic problem with putting these conversions on an NPC, let's make the following Iksar cultural smithing recipes which work in the Iksar forge and have almost the exact same effect:&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;3 Small Brick of Yttrium Ore + 1 Cabilis essence + 1 small brick of skyiron +&amp;nbsp; cabilisan smithy hammer -&amp;gt; master's twoscale skyiron bar + cabilisan smithy hammer&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; (Trivial 182)&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;3 Midnight Stone + 1 Cabilis essence + 1 small brick of skyiron +&amp;nbsp; cabilisan smithy hammer -&amp;gt; master's twoscale skyiron bar + cabilisan smithy hammer&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; (Trivial 182)&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;3 Pile of Gravel + 1 Cabilis essence + 1 small brick of skyiron +&amp;nbsp; cabilisan smithy hammer -&amp;gt; master's twoscale skyiron bar + cabilisan smithy hammer&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; (Trivial 182)&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;This sort of approach would require 3 new recipies at each of the 3 levels for each of the 3 types of base drops for each of the 11 races: once again 297 new formula, this time in various cultural tradeskill containers.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Would this completely address the disparity between races? No.&amp;nbsp; Would the TS community accept this as a work-around? I think so.&amp;nbsp; It also would keep some races cultural more expensive than others ... but the incredible frustration felt by some races in acquiring raw materials&amp;nbsp;should be alleviated.&amp;nbsp; It also has the advantage of allowing conversion, so if one race's master armor is more available at a given time, all races have the option of working with that material.&amp;nbsp; Of course, as a result, the demand will increase for the cheaper one&amp;nbsp; ... ;-7&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Just my 2 cents.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
